00:17.550 --> 00:19.249
<i>Violent crime
increased in many</i>

00:19.251 --> 00:20.650
<i>of the nation's largest cities
in 2017...</i>

00:20.652 --> 00:22.786
<i>...second
year in a row that metro areas</i>

00:22.788 --> 00:25.621
<i>saw jumps in robbery, homicide,
and aggravated assault.</i>

00:25.623 --> 00:27.423
<i>Theories of
the increased crime include</i>

00:27.425 --> 00:28.859
<i>violence associated with drugs,</i>

00:28.861 --> 00:30.627
<i>the high number of guns
in many US cities,</i>

00:30.629 --> 00:32.463
<i>gang violence and retaliation,
and even</i>

00:32.465 --> 00:34.330
<i>problems originating
from conflicts on social media.</i>

00:34.332 --> 00:35.799
<i>So what
happened to the city?</i>

00:35.801 --> 00:37.733
<i>I remember when you could take
a walk at night.</i>

00:37.735 --> 00:39.602
<i>When you
could take a walk at night?</i>

00:39.604 --> 00:41.271
<i>The city's always been bad,</i>

00:41.273 --> 00:42.605
<i>and our police forces
are overworked</i>

00:42.607 --> 00:44.274
<i>and underpaid,
what can we expect?</i>

00:44.276 --> 00:45.576
<i>We expect to feel safe.</i>

00:45.578 --> 00:46.876
<i>We expect to walk outside</i>

00:46.878 --> 00:48.479
<i>and not be in danger.</i>

00:48.481 --> 00:50.546
<i>Is that really too much to ask?</i>

00:50.548 --> 00:52.315
<i>Metro police
caution that it's too</i>

00:52.317 --> 00:53.650
<i>early to know
whether increases seen</i>

00:53.652 --> 00:55.552
<i>over the last two years
are coincidences</i>

00:55.554 --> 00:56.887
<i>or the beginning of
a sustained increase</i>

00:56.889 --> 00:58.421
<i>in overall crime rates</i>

00:58.423 --> 00:59.589
<i>around the country.</i>

